      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) directly maps to clinical hemolysis threshold; no surrogate substitution.",
      "rationale": "The CFD QoI is NIH in mg/dL, identical to the clinical acceptance criterion. No intermediate surrogate quantities are used. The hemolysis power-law model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) is applied to Lagrangian particle trajectories, producing NIH directly comparable to bench measurements."
