      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; checklist-based review documented.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of simulation setup conducted by a second CFD engineer not involved in model construction. Boundary condition assignment, turbulence model selection, and rotating reference frame configuration all verified. No use errors identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model selected based on literature evidence for rotating blood-contacting flows; model form uncertainty bounded.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published benchmark studies for centrifugal pump hemolysis. Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model calibrated against bovine blood data. Model form uncertainty estimated via comparison with alternative Lagrangian hemolysis models; spread bounded at ±15% NIH."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs characterized with probability distributions; Monte Carlo UQ propagated through full simulation pipeline.",
      "rationale": "Ten uncertain inputs identified: fluid viscosity, hematocrit, inlet velocity profile shape, rotational speed tolerance, pump clearance gap, hemolysis model exponents (alpha, beta), exposure time integration step, and outlet pressure. Distributions assigned from measurement data and literature. Monte Carlo UQ with 10,000 samples propagated through the hemolysis prediction pipeline; 95th-percentile NIH remains below clinical threshold."
    },
    {
