      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sufficient experimental replicates to characterize measurement variability; minimum n=3 per operating point.",
      "rationale": "Five replicates per operating point conducted (n=25 total). Coefficient of variation in measured NIH across replicates: 4.1–9.7%. Measurement uncertainty characterized and incorporated into validation comparison."
